data.title: Bluprynt secures $4.25M in oversubscribed Seed round led by Valor Capital Group, Robinhood, Coinbase Ventures, and others.
data.description: The compliance operating system for digital assets, Bluprynt, revealed the completion of its Seed round, securing a total of $4.25 million. Valor Capital Group spearheaded the oversubscribed funding round, joined by Cultivation Capital, and notable investors such as Robinhood, Coinbase Ventures, Quona Capital, Kazea, Flourish Ventures, Radical Investments, and Selah Ventures. Ricardo Marino and other prominent individual and strategic investors also participated in this round.

data.title: iNav AI tool by Northwell Health speeds pancreatic cancer detection, cutting biopsy to diagnosis time in half.
data.description: In New Hyde Park, N.Y., a study published in The Oncologist revealed that pancreatic cancer poses challenges in early identification, with over 80% of patients diagnosed at an advanced stage. This limits treatment options significantly. Nonetheless, research on iNav, an in-house AI clinical tool developed by Northwell Health, indicates promising advancements. iNav has demonstrated the capability to reduce the duration from biopsy to diagnosis by fifty percent. As a result, treatment timelines for patients can be accelerated, potentially improving outcomes for individuals affected by this challenging disease.

data.title: Dell to release Q4 earnings on Feb. 26, analysts predict $3.53 EPS and $31.75 billion revenue. Dell shares closed at $123.48.
data.description: Dell Technologies Inc. is set to announce its Q4 earnings on February 26. Analysts predict earnings of $3.53 per share, an increase from $2.68 per share last year. Revenue for the quarter is expected to be around $31.75 billion, up from $23.93 billion a year ago. The company also launched the Dell PowerEdge XR9700, a specialized server for outdoor environments. Dell's stock rose by 3.1% to $123.48. For more information and updates on analyst ratings, visit the Benzinga website.

data.title: Abitibiwinni First Nation seeks input in purchase of Hecla Quebec & Casa Berardi Mine by Orezone Gold Corp in Feb 26, 2026.
data.description: In Pikogan, QC, on February 26, 2026, the Abitibiwinni First Nation is urging Hecla Mining Company (NYSE: HL) and Orezone Gold Corporation (TSX: ORE) (ASX: ORE) (OTCQX: ORZCF) to oversee a seamless and just transition that honors its wishes.
